# qmog.cpp

## Philosophy

- Think from first principles.
- Prefer the simplest correct solution.
- Every line of code should justify its existence.
- Favor deletion over addition when both solve the problem.
- Reduce complexity whenever you touch code.
- Simplify before optimizing.

## Code

- Make the smallest change that fully solves the problem.
- Do not introduce new dependencies without asking first.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Preserve existing behavior unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer the C++ standard library over third party libraries.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions, wrappers, helper functions, and configuration.
- Optimize only after correctness and clarity.

## Git

- Start every feature, fix, or experiment from a branch off `main`.

## Responses

- Be concise.
- Answer only what was asked.
- Explain complex topics from first principles, one step at a time.
- Use plain, direct language.
- Do not use analogies.
- Only provide code when requested.
- When writing code, prefer the smallest complete solution.
